what-it-does: Checks for duplicate members in a typing.Literal[] slice.
why-is-this-bad: Duplicate literal members are redundant and should be removed.
example:
foo: Literal["a", "b", "a"]



Use instead:


foo: Literal["a", "b"]
fix-safety:
This rule's fix is marked as safe, unless the type annotation contains comments.


Note that while the fix may flatten nested literals into a single top-level literal,
the semantics of the annotation will remain unchanged.
